msgid "Cache Volume"
msgstr ""

# df3a315ed539432cad39958580374a19
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:25
msgid ""
"Each configured :ref:`cache-volume` receives a complete set of statistics"
" from |TS|. They are differentiated from each other by the incrementing "
"number that is part of the statistic name. The volume number begins at "
":literal:`0` and increments by :literal:`1` for each additional volume."
msgstr ""

# 46872641f492416fa20e95d3cdbefe01
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:30
msgid ""
"The statistics are documented in this section using the default volume "
"number in a configuration with only one cache volume: :literal:`0`."
msgstr ""

# f14b7f5bfd9d4f97abe59ee909022ac4
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:37
msgid "Represents the total number of bytes allocated for the cache volume."
msgstr ""

# 9db065bdc3f14673a1ed52d07d571138
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:43
msgid ""
"Represents the number of bytes in this cache volume which are occupied by"
" cache objects."
msgstr ""

# 4bf4e74215a44469b70b109854bb24a2
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:52
msgid ""
"Represents the total number of directory entries which have been "
"allocated in this cache volume."
msgstr ""

# 3ddbf060b90640a39dcc6a38208ab3be
#: ../../admin-guide/monitoring/statistics/core/cache-volume.en.rst:58
msgid ""
"Represents the number of allocated directory entries in this cache volume"
" which are in use."
msgstr ""

